RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 l bs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE MOUNTAIN took a quick lead and moved toward the inside to rate the pace, contested the advantage just off the rail on the turn and was steadily handled to hold on well. AWESOME MOON chased, raced close in the three path on the turn and dueled clear in second mid-stretch. MICHEAUX chased inside, rounded the turn near the rail, relented second mid-stretch but held on for third. JACKYSINTHECASTLE exchanged contact with Stowe Patrol leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail and ran evenly in the lane. I SHALLBE RELEASED chased, rounded the turn in the five path and ran evenly in the stretch. LET'S DO THIS broke a step slow, gave chase through the backstretch and rounded the turn about the four path, but showed little in the lane. STOWE PATROL exchanged contact with Jackysinthecastle leaving the gate, gave only brief early chase, raced wide on the turn and was eased in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Let's Do This
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow break,chased,4p turn,little in lane

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Mountain
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated pace inside,off rail turn,held well driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 13100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LION OF THE SEA accelerated to the lead leaving the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, drew clear toward the five sixteenths, widened at the rail on the turn and was kept sharp through the lane. BILLINGSGATE gave chase, raced three wide on the turn and dueled through the stretch for second. D TACHYON chased, raced off the rail on the turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for second. HE IS BONAFIDE exchanged contact with Dinner Bell leaving the gate, dueled with a brief early lead then gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, dropped back toward the five sixteenths, raced in the three path on the turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. POLITICAL DECISION gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. CHIPPEWA'S CASTLE chased through the backstretch, raced in the six path on the turn and showed little in the lane. LITTLE BAY chased, rounded the turn about the four path, was carried out into the lane and weakened. DINNER BELL exchanged contact with He Is Bonafide leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn, drifted toward the head of the lane and weakened. VICTORIOUS BEAR gave chase outside and rounded the turn about the seven path.

ENTRY.NAME: Lion of the Sea
ENTRY.COMMENT: up past 7/16,set pressured pace,clear near 5/16,widen,kept sharp

ENTRY.NAME: Little Bay
ENTRY.OWNER: Cunningham Matthew and Vick Timothy M

ENTRY.NAME: Billingsgate
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER SINCE DECEMBER 17, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lb s.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 17 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOONLIT SHADOW raced with the early pace three deep, challenged two deep into the backstretch and dueled at even terms from that point, contested the edge through the far turn, drew clear past the eighth pole and edged away in the lane. JAMESTOWN ROAD raced with the pace inside, dueled at even terms leaving the half mile pole, contested at a close disadvantage at the rail on the far turn, dropped back inside the eighth pole and flattened stride later yards. AZZURRA settled off the rail on the opening turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn, dug in at the head of the land and just lasted for third. SENECA ROCKS rounded the first turn about the three path, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. SECRET CASTLE raced with the early pace two deep and between horses, dropped back at the nine sixteenths, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths but flattened at the rail on the far turn. UNRULY JULIE saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Jamestown Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace,dueled 1/2,close rail turn,flattened later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Moonlit Shadow
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace,challenged 1/2,dueled even terms,edged away lane

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Timothy C. Grams & Judith A. Grams

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 15200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 17, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since December 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLEARLY VISIBLE came away rank and inward and made contact with Congress Hall then saved ground well back, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, steadily improved at the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady encouragement through the stretch and took the nod under the wire. CRUZ IN THE CASTLE raced with the pace two deep, was pressured with the advantage toward the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the turn, dug in under steady right hand stretch encouragement but drifted outward in deep stretch and missed the nod under the wire. THUNDERTURTLE settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase into the backstretch and rounded the far turn about the four path, dug in from the head of the lane but was forced out and had to steady late stretch. TIZ MICHELLE'S WAY raced with the early pace, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but dropped back at the rail nearing the quarter, rounded the far turn off the rail and flattened later yards. CONGRESS HALL was bumped inward and into Ravenel leaving the gate, rounded the first turn in the three path and gave chase toward the three eighths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn then flattened in the lane. SAX saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four and five paths on the far turn and showed little in the lane. RAVENEL was bumped leaving the gate then stalked from the four path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path then weakened into the lane. MAE SAI PRINCESS stalked from the three path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn. SHEMADEMELUCKY showed little response. The Stewards reviewed a claim of foul against the rider of Cruz In The Castle for late stretch interference, lodged by the rider of Thunderturtle, and disqualified the former to third place for forcing the latter outward through late yards.

ENTRY.NAME: Thunderturtle
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased 1/2,4p far turn,forced out steadying late

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Michelle's Way
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace,chased 7/16,dropped back rail 1/4,flattened late yards

ENTRY.NAME: Congress Hall
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,3p 1st turn,chased 3/8,5p far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 14400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMINCHARGENOW gave chase and took the lead two deep midway on the turn, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn and held on well. JUJU ON DA BEAT chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, altered course from the heels of Bowmans Lazy Girl toward mid-stretch and dug in from there to take second later yards. LADY GANGSTER gave chase, rounded the turn in the three and four paths and came along to take third late. LOCKDOWN VANNA chased, raced at the rail on the turn and flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. BOWMANS LAZY GIRL took over on the chute and moved to the inside to set a pressured pace, but was caught midway on the turn and weakened the final sixteenth. SUNSET QUEEN chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, eased out leaving the turn but showed little in the lane. S S CASINO GIRL gave chase while saving ground. ITSUPTOME was never a factor. JUST ASK ME stumbled after the start, gave chase through the backstretch and rounded the turn about the four path, then drifted toward the head of the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Sunset Queen
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,eased out 1/8,little in lane

ENTRY.NAME: Juju On Da Beat
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,altered course 1/16,up 2nd later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Iminchargenow
ENTRY.OWNER: Ali Andrew and Schottroffe Edward T

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Andrew Earl Ali & Edward Thomas Schottroffe

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Starter Allowance Purse 20700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 17, 2021. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 17 Allowed 4 l bs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACADIAN GIRL rated a short lead inside, was urged into the far turn, widened at the rail and was steadily handled in the lane. DIVINE FASHION saved ground off the pace, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and had to settle for second best. VOLNAY stalked the earlier pace two deep, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and took the nod for third in the final stride. TEQUILA FOG settled off the rail on the opening turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly down the lane. HIDDEN IDENTITY saved ground close to the pace but was boxed at the rail nearing the half mile pole, picked up the chase past the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and flattened the final sixteenth. RED QUEEN raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and weakened in the lane. MI CLEOPATRA AND I closed toward contention three wide through the front stretch, raced in the three and four paths on the opening turn but showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Acadian Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated short lead,urged into turn,widened rail,steady urging lane

ENTRY.NAME: Red Queen
ENTRY.OWNER: Honoring Luke Stables and Kenworthy John C

ENTRY.NAME: Mi Cleopatra and I
ENTRY.OWNER: Bush Racing Stable and Liberty House Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: It's Only Money S. CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 102. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR REGISTERED ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. $50 nominations close Wednesday, June 7, 2023. $50 to enter with a purse of $75,000 Added. Entries close Wednesday, June 14, 2023 by the usual time of closing. The added monies and a ll fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight: Three Year Olds 116 lbs.; Older 123 lbs. Field will be limited to ten starters with up to four alternates. Preference to those horses having accum ulated the highest 2022-2023 earnings at the time of closing of entries. Trophy to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE ROO ROO engaged in close chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and drew clear later yards. GOLDEN KEY drew clear leaving the chute and set a pressured pace, contested the advantage at the rail on the turn, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn but was caught mid-stretch and just lasted for second. PENGUIN POWER gave close chase through the backstretch, raced in the four path on the turn, dug in from the head of the lane, finished well and just missed second. DERBY DAY DREAMS gave chase through the backstretch, raced two deep on the turn and finished well. ICING came away awkwardly then gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane. NICO chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn and finished well. MATH MAN MARCO gave close early chase but weakened in the four path entering the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Little Roo Roo
ENTRY.COMMENT: close chase,off rail turn,up 1/16,clear later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Golden Key
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear leaving chute,set pressured pace,met 1/16,just lasted 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Penguin Power
ENTRY.COMMENT: close chase,4p turn,dug in lane,just missed 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SISTER SPIRIT saved ground on the first turn, started a bid past the seven sixteenths pole and circled rivals six wide on the far turn, dug in for the lead passing the sixteenth pole and drew away later yards. JACCACI was bumped leaving the gate, raced in the five path the first turn and picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths and dug in to take second the final yards. RATIONALMILLENNIAL came away awkwardly then saved ground, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, clipped the heels of Hearditall midway on the far turn, quickly recovered stride and left the turn three wide, angled to the rail mid-stretch and dug in to take the nod for third under the wire. PRETTY SPECTACULAR rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase past the half mile pole and raced in the four path of the far turn, then finished evenly to pass rivals. SPUNKY ZOEY ducked out and made contact with Jaccaci leaving the gate, raced in the three path on the first turn and picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, raced close two deep through the far turn then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. CURLIN'S DOVE stalked three wide on the first turn, challenged and took the lead leaving the seven sixteenths pole, contested the advantage at the rail on the far turn but was met mid-stretch and weakened. LADY WHISTLEDOWN raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn five wide then flattened in the lane. RIGHT TO ASSEMBLE rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path, angled to the rail into the lane and weakened. HEARDITALL stalked off the rail, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, had her heels clipped midway on the far turn and weakened. CONDUCTANCE was hustled with the lead early, ceded control and gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, steadied in tight and brushed the rail approaching the quarter pole and raced boxed in through the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Rationalmillennial
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward break,saved ground,chased 3/8,clipped heels mid turn

ENTRY.NAME: Conductance
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled early,met leaving 7/16,brushed rail near 1/4,boxed turn

ENTRY.NAME: Hearditall
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 3/8,heels clipped mid turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Jaccaci
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumpbed break,5p 1st turn,chased 7/16,3& 4p far turn,up 2nd late

ENTRY.NAME: Sister Spirit
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid past 7/16,circled 6wd far turn,up 1/16,drew away

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Wasabi Ventures Stables, LLC, Connie S.Black, Kyle Scribne
